<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFArcher.2C_Jules1973.2C_pub.2007">Archer, Jules (1973, pub.2007). <i>The Plot to Seize the White House</i>. Skyhorse Publishing.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Plot+to+Seize+the+White+House&amp;rft.aulast=Archer%2C+Jules&amp;rft.au=Archer%2C+Jules&amp;rft.date=1973%2C+pub.2007&amp;rft.pub=Skyhorse+Publishing&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Business_Plot"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span><a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1602390363" class="internal">ISBN 1-60239-036-3</a>, <a href="http://www.clubhousewreckards.com/plot/plottoseizethewhitehouse.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.clubhousewreckards.com/plot/plottoseizethewhitehouse.htm" rel="nofollow">Book Information and Chapter Summaries</a>, <a href="http://portland.indymedia.org/en/2004/10/298735.shtml" class="external text" title="http://portland.indymedia.org/en/2004/10/298735.shtml" rel="nofollow">Executive summary and/or extensive quotes of Jules Archer's book</a> on the subject, mostly on Butler's Censored Testimony Concerning Attempts to Bribe Him Into the Plot.</li>
